001package edu.cnm.deepdive.leavemealone.model.entity;
002
003
004import androidx.annotation.NonNull;
005import androidx.annotation.Nullable;
006import androidx.room.ColumnInfo;
007import androidx.room.Embedded;
008import androidx.room.Entity;
009import androidx.room.Index;
010import androidx.room.PrimaryKey;
011import edu.cnm.deepdive.leavemealone.model.pojo.GPSCoord;
012import java.time.Instant;
013
014@Entity(
015    tableName = "location",
016    indices = {})
017public class Location {
018
019    @PrimaryKey(autoGenerate = true)
020    @ColumnInfo(name = "location_id")
021    private long id;
022
023    @ColumnInfo(name = "alert_id")
024    @Nullable
025    private long alertId;
026
027    @ColumnInfo(name = "secure", index = true)
028    private boolean secure;
029
030    @Embedded
031    private GPSCoord gpsCoord;
032
033    /**
034     * Returns the id of a particular location
035     * @return
036     */
037    public long getId() {
038        return id;
039    }
040
041    /**
042     * This annotates an individual location with an id
043     * @param id
044     */
045    public void setId(long id) {
046        this.id = id;
047    }
048
049    /**
050     * This returns the alert_id of a particular location
051     * @return
052     */
053    public long getAlertId() {
054        return alertId;
055    }
056
057    /**
058     * This annotates an individual location with its associated alert_id
059     * @param alertId
060     */
061    public void setAlertId(long alertId) {
062        this.alertId = alertId;
063    }
064
065    /**
066     * This returns the secure status of a location
067     * @return
068     */
069    public boolean isSecure() {
070        return secure;
071    }
072
073    /**
074     * This annotates a location with a boolena secure status
075     * @param secure
076     */
077    public void setSecure(boolean secure) {
078        this.secure = secure;
079    }
080
081    /**
082     * This returns the GPS coordinates of a location
083     *
084     * @return
085     */
086    public GPSCoord getGpsCoord() {
087        return gpsCoord;
088    }
089
090    /**
091     * This annotates a location with a set of GPS coordinates
092     * @param gpsCoord
093     */
094    public void setGpsCoord(GPSCoord gpsCoord) {
095        this.gpsCoord = gpsCoord;
096    }
097}
